二、指定教科書及參考資料 Textbooks and Reference(請修課同學遵守智慧財產權，不得非法影印)


●指定教科書 Required TextsThere is no set textbook for this course. In class we will use materials from a variety of sources, including Intermediate GEPT listening exams. Students will also be required to create their own listening materials for their in-class presentations.
		●參考書資料暨網路資源 Reference Books and Online ResourcesListening activities and resources will be drawn from a variety of resources.Live Interactive English Magazine, VOA Learning English, CNN Magazine, Youtube etc.Useful websites:A list of corresponding units in CNN is available at the Language Center Homepage (http://www.scu.edu.tw/language/index.htm).http://www.longman.com/summithttp://www.englishpage.com/ (grammar help)http://owl.english.purdue.edu/http://www.merriam-webster.com/info/07words.htmhttp://www.refdesk.com/factgram.htmlhttp://www.breakingnewsenglish.com/http://www.voanews.com/specialenglish/index.cfmhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/science/leonardo/thinker_quiz/


三、教學目標 Objectives


The primary goal of the course is to develop listening skills. This will be achieved by developing the ability to successfully listen to a variety of recordings (textbook, CDs, TV, videos etc) and cultivating the ability to analyze what has been listened to. The course will be taught in English and emphasis will be on using English for communication at all times. This class will take a communicative, task-based approach to learning English. Students will take part in group activities and perform collaborative learning tasks. Interaction in English with peers and the instructor will comprise a major part of this course and assessment.　


四、課程內容 Course Description


●整體敘述 Overall DescriptionClass lecture, pair-interacting, group discussion, presentation and activities etc…CNN will be used in class and for assessment. A list of corresponding units in CNN is available at the Language Center Homepage (http://www.scu.edu.tw/language/index.htm).

